<h3>Phi Phi Island</h3>
<p>The twin Phi Phi islands, comprised of Phi Phi Don and Phi Phi Ley, are located 45 kilometers to the southeast of Phuket. They are famous for their stunning beaches, clear turquoise waters, and towering limestone cliffs rising out of the sea. A popular anchorage is Maya Bay, which was used as a location in the film “The Beach”.</p>
</div>
